## 4. Platform Stream Primitives (Moved)

> **This content has been moved to the canonical [Stream Architecture Specification v0.8.1](../architecture/STREAM_ARCHITECTURE_SPEC.md).**
>
> The Stream Architecture Spec v0.8.1 defines:
> - **Typed stream patterns**: event, state, signal, curated, log, media, transaction, mpc_session (В§2)
> - **Growing context pipelines**: Multi-stage widening ESF schemas (В§3)
> - **ESCIR pattern annotations**: stream_pattern, topology, governance, sla (В§4)
> - **Stream operators**: filter, transform, aggregate, throttle, join, materialize, pipeline (В§13)
> - **Audience filters**: Crypto-enforced field visibility with governance auto-generation (В§14)
> - **Adaptive observation**: StreamSight dynamic telemetry L0-L3 (В§15)
> - **Governance lifecycle**: Genesis, lex activation, protocol upgrade, emergency (В§16)
> - **Transport & addressing**: IPv6, SRv6, geo-avoidance, ESP tunnels (В§17)
> - **DNS & naming**: gTLD hybrid DNS+lex resolution (В§18)
> - **High availability**: SLA-driven HA clusters with witness braiding (В§19)
> - **Multi-party computation**: Garbled circuits, PSI, threshold decryption (В§20)
> - **Deployment pipeline**: Growing context release flow with PoVC (В§21)
> - **Circuit references**: Lex-path-based URI scheme (В§22)
> - **Codegen contract**: Rust and Verilog generation per annotation (В§5)
> - **Typed governance primitives**: SOC2, PCI-DSS, HIPAA, GDPR (В§6)
> - **Lex hierarchy & typed consensus**: N-level with governance cascade (В§7)
> - **Declarative SLAs**: Latency, durability, geo, throughput targets (В§8)
> - **Multi-language SDK design**: Rust, Swift, Kotlin, Go, TypeScript, Python (В§9)
>
> Queue Streams (`estream-queue`) and State Maps (`estream-map`) are now expressed as
> **event streams** and **state streams** respectively, implemented as SmartCircuit-driven
> typed stream patterns on lex FIFO and KV storage primitives.
>
> See the [Stream Architecture Implementation Plan](../architecture/STREAM_ARCHITECTURE_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md)
> for the phased build roadmap.

